at rugby camp when I was 12

243
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:19,360
and given the sportsmanship trophy at 14.

244
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:22,320
Not only am I
the captain of the rugby team,

245
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:26,960
but I am also incredibly handsome
and have a very nice--

246
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:28,360
Oi… [chuckles]

247
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,960
Okay, but you have to let me talk
about how lovely and kind

248
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:33,640
and brave and smart you are.

249
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:41,000
Maybe you should get a part-time job
or a volunteering job or something.

250
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,520
Yeah. Yeah, maybe.

251
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,920
{\an8}Rugby's good, but

252
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,560
{\an8}you should have something
outside of school just for you.

253
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:52,960
Maybe then you'll start to realize
how great you are.

254
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:57,480
[school bell rings]

255
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:07,640
Hey. You okay?

256
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:12,240
Did you wanna talk to me about something?

257
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:16,160
[intriguing music playing]

258
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:21,960
[Charlie] <i>Growing up queer can be</i>
<i>so isolating and scary.</i>

259
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:24,960
Especially in a single-sex school.

260
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:29,520
You're an easy target for bullies.
You might struggle to make friends.

261
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:33,520
Queer kids need a space they feel
supported by older students and teachers.

262
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:37,320
The thing is, Charlie,
it sets a precedent.

263
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:41,280
We don't have any other clubs
for… social groups.

264
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:43,280
Well, maybe this could be the first.

265
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:47,000
I don't think I can commit to this
right now, Charlie.

266
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:50,840
Let's wait a few months,
and we'll revisit.

267
00:16:53,520 --> 00:16:54,360
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

268
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,120
<i>♪ Hey ♪</i>

269
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,000
<i>♪ Yeah… ♪</i>

270
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:01,240
He's got a mustache. [chuckles]

271
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:05,960
[Michael] I'm training
with a new coach up north.

272
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:10,560
Also teaching kids how to skate,
which is endlessly entertaining.

273
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:13,640
He won't say it, but he's training
to qualify for the Winter Olympics.

274
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:15,080
Wait, are you serious?

275
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:17,960
There's more to it,
but, yeah, that's the general idea.

276
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:20,160
-So you're just back for the weekend?
-[Michael] Yeah.

277
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:23,080
I mean, three months
without seeing Tori, so…

278
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:26,040
-Yeah, sounds rough.
-[Michael] I mean, we're okay though.

279
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:28,000
I mean, there's…
there's her life and my life,

280
00:17:28,080 --> 00:17:32,640
and when we're together, it's…
it's like… [whooshing, mimics explosion]

281
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:36,000
But when we're apart, it's like…

282
00:17:36,080 --> 00:17:39,080
Whoo… [mimics explosion]

283
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:41,400
Also, phones exist, so…

284
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:42,920
[Charlie chuckles softly]

285
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:48,680
[Nick] I think you need to finish this
'cause I'm struggling.

286
00:17:48,760 --> 00:17:50,360
Wait, if you hold the end, I can…

287
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:53,520
[pensive music playing]

288
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,800
[Nick breathing quickly]

289
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:03,560
Hey.

290
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:05,960
Hey, what's up? What's going on?

291
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,480
[Nick breathes shakily]

292
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:14,360
I had a dream you died.

293
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:16,040
[Charlie] What?

294
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:19,720
[Nick gasps]

295
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:21,960
Sorry, I…

296
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:27,600
{\an8}It's so stupid. I just…
It felt really real. [sniffles]

297
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:29,960
Sorry.

298
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:32,760
-It's okay.
-[breathing heavily]

299
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:35,200
It's not real. I'm right here.

300
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:45,080
-[Charlie] Can you…
-[Nick] Got it.

301
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:46,200
[Charlie] Thank you.

302
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:48,040
[Tao] I'll take that.

303
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:49,920
-[Darcy] I'll get that.
-[Charlie] Great.

304
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,880
[indistinct chattering]

305
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:57,320
All right. Santa Claus is coming to town.

306
00:18:57,400 --> 00:19:00,320
-[Elle] Yes, please.
-[Isaac] You look a bit like him.

307
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:04,160
Everyone say cheers and thank you to Nick
for being able to legally buy alcohol.

308
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:06,680
I know that's the only reason
you keep me around.

309
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:08,160
[Imogen] Oh, don't say that.

310
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:09,680
Charlie looks fit.

311
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:13,280
It's the self-confidence.
It's transformative.

312
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:16,240
I think when you know yourself,
it's really powerful.

313
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:20,640
-Speaking of, I wanted to--
-Okay, everybody, we are Queer Intentions.

314
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:22,200
-[cheering]
-Whoo! Whoo-whoo!

315
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:25,640
We're here to play you some music tonight,
so who's ready to rock?

316
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:27,280
I'm ready! I'm ready!

317
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:31,520
[band playing
"I Only Want to Be With You"]

318
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:33,640
-Who's dancing?
-[Nick] I like this one.

319
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:35,440
-[Tara] Let's dance.
-What, already?

320
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:38,080
-Yes. Come on, Nicholas!
-I've just got… Wait.

321
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:39,440
[Tara whooping]

322
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:43,280
♪ <i>I only know I never wanna let you go </i>♪

323
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:47,240
♪ <i>'Cause you started something</i>
<i>Oh, can't you see </i>♪

324
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:50,840
♪ <i>That ever since we met</i>
<i>You've had a hold on me? </i>♪

325
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:54,280
♪ <i>It happens to be true </i>♪

326
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:58,120
<i>♪ I only wanna be with you ♪</i>

327
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,960
♪ <i>You stopped to smile at me</i>… ♪

328
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:02,080
Yeah, Charlie!

329
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:05,640
[Sahar] ♪ <i>Asked me if I'd care to dance </i>♪

330
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:09,280
♪ <i>I fell into your open arms </i>♪

331
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:13,400
♪ <i>I didn't stand a chance </i>♪

332
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:17,640
♪ <i>Now listen, honey</i>
<i>I just wanna be beside you everywhere</i>… ♪

333
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:20,480
-Go on, Charlie!
-[Christian] Nick! Hey, Nick. Tequila!

334
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,720
-[Nick] Ah…
-Sort him out. Sort him out.

335
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:24,000
-Here, bro.
-Okay.

336
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:24,920
-You ready?
-Yep.

337
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,120
-Right. Everyone.
-Right.

338
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:29,120
-Cheers.
-[others] Cheers.

339
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:32,360
-[boy coughs]
-Oh my…

340
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:37,080
♪ <i>I only wanna be with you </i>♪

341
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:38,360
-I'm okay.
-Let's go again.

342
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:40,040
-No, I'm okay.
-Come on!

343
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:42,840
Please. Come on. One more.

344
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:45,760
-[Sai] Come on.
-All right, okay.

345
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:46,880
-You ready?
-Yeah.

346
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:47,800
Right.

347
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:50,560
-And cheers, boys.
-Cheers.

348
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:57,280
♪ <i>Now listen, honey</i>
<i>I just want to be beside you everywhere </i>♪

349
00:20:57,360 --> 00:21:01,080
♪ <i>As long as we're together</i>
<i>Honey, I don't care </i>♪

350
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:04,760
♪ <i>'Cause you've started something</i>
<i>Oh, can't you see </i>♪

351
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:08,400
♪ <i>That ever since we met</i>
<i>You've got a hold on me? </i>♪

352
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:11,840
♪ <i>No matter what you do </i>♪

353
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:15,800
-♪ <i>I only wanna be with you </i>♪
-[Christian] Yeah!

354
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:19,080
[Sahar] ♪ <i>No matter what you do </i>♪

355
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:22,960
♪ <i>I only, only, only, only </i>♪

356
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:26,840
♪ <i>I only wanna be with you </i>♪

357
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:28,840
[cheering]

358
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:31,320
One more song! One more song!

359
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:33,480
Um, so we have got another song for you.

360
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:36,640
It's a Christmas song
'cause the manager says we have to.

361
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:38,640
But you might recognize this one.

362
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:43,240
-[a cappella] ♪ <i>Deck the halls with</i>… ♪
-Oh, I love this one.

363
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:48,440
♪ <i>'Tis the season to be jolly</i>…♪

364
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:49,600
[girl] Have we met?

365
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:53,360
Yeah, I think, uh, I think we maybe went
to drama school together. Yeah.

366
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:56,240
-Nice to meet you.
<i>-♪ Don we now our gay apparel</i>… <i>♪</i>

367
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:57,920
The band is so good.

368
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:00,400
Yeah. Yeah.
That's… that's actually my boyfriend.

369
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:01,800
Oh, hi.

370
00:22:04,360 --> 00:22:10,000
-[band plays rock version]
-♪ <i>See the blazing yule before us </i>♪

371
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:15,160
♪ <i>Strike the harp and join the chorus </i>♪

372
00:22:16,320 --> 00:22:19,280
♪ <i>Fast away the old year passes </i>♪

373
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:22,360
[all] ♪ <i>Fa la la la, la la la </i>♪

374
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:25,280
[Sahar] ♪ <i>Hail the new year</i>
<i>Lads and lasses </i>♪

375
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:28,120
[all] ♪ <i>Fa la la la, la la la </i>♪

376
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:31,400
♪ <i>Sing we joyous all together </i>♪

377
00:22:31,480 --> 00:22:34,280
[all] ♪ <i>Fa la la la, la la la </i>♪

378
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:37,320
[Sahar] ♪ <i>Heedless of the wind</i>
<i>And weather </i>♪

379
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:40,200
[all] ♪ <i>Fa la la la, la la la</i>… ♪

380
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:44,400
-I love you! Oh!
<i>-♪ See the blazing yule before us ♪</i>

381
00:22:46,080 --> 00:22:49,600
-♪ <i>Strike the harp and join the chorus </i>♪
-[Nick giggling]

382
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:52,280
[all] ♪ <i>Fa la la la la, la la la la </i>♪

383
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:58,240
-[Sahar] ♪ <i>Follow me in merry measure </i>♪
-[all] ♪ <i>Fa la la la la la, la la la </i>♪

384
00:22:58,320 --> 00:22:59,520
[Sahar] ♪ <i>While I tell </i>♪

385
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:01,280
<i>- </i>♪ <i>Of Yuletide treasure </i>♪
-Whoo!

386
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:03,160
[urinating]

387
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:04,880
[sighs]

388
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:08,360
[toilet flushing]

389
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:09,600
[zipper closing]

390
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,120
[sniffs]

391
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:17,800
[faucet running]

392
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,880
[indistinct chattering]

393
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:37,600
[Elle] It's like you don't even care
about my dreams.

394
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:41,040
[Tao] I respect your dreams,
but not coming to visit me at all?

395
00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:44,360
I mean, Berlin's not even that far.
It's two hours by plane.

396
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:46,440
I don't know what you want me to say, Tao.

397
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:49,760
I'm sorry I'm not rich and have money
to get on a flight every two min--

398
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:53,880
Hey, hey, hey, hey. You need to talk
to each other. Like, communicate.

399
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:59,040
It's… it's just about communicating
and, and, and saying what's in there.

400
00:23:59,120 --> 00:24:02,560
That's… that's all that matters,
and then you'll be able to connect--

401
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:04,000
Yeah, okay, Nick.

402
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:06,240
No, if you love each other, it's easy.

403
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:08,600
You know, me and Charlie,
we love each other--

404
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:11,520
Yeah, we get it.
You and Charlie are perfect, all right?

405
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:14,760
It's… it's just not the time
right now, Nick.

406
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:17,920
All right.

407
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:23,840
You guys were <i>so </i>good.

408
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:26,640
Um, I've always wanted to learn
how to play the drums.

409
00:24:26,720 --> 00:24:29,080
-Oh, well, you… you still could.
-Yeah…

410
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:31,720
It just… it seems so hard,
though, you know?

411
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:34,680
Any drumming advice?

412
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:35,760
[Charlie chuckles]

413
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:38,360
Just… just practice.

414
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:40,400
[last orders bell rings in distance]

415
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:42,640
Hey, you all right?

416
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:46,440
Charlie was just giving me
some drumming tips.

417
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:50,440
Really? 'Cause it looks like
you were just flirting with my boyfriend.

418
00:24:50,520 --> 00:24:52,960
Well, we were just having
a conversation, so…

419
00:24:53,040 --> 00:24:55,720
Okay, well, conversation's over.

420
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:58,040
Nick!

421
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:01,480
-Nick, are you okay?
-He was flirting with you, so…

422
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:03,640
Yeah, I know he was. I can handle myself.

423
00:25:03,720 --> 00:25:06,600
I didn't march over when that girl
was flirting with you earlier, did I?

424
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:08,400
No, but that's different, isn't it?

425
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:11,520
-Tao, can we just talk, please?
-[Tao] No, I don't want to.

426
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:13,640
-[Elle] We can figure this out.
-[Tao] Nothing to say.

427
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:16,840
-I'm gonna get another drink.
-[Charlie] No. You've had enough.

428
00:25:16,920 --> 00:25:18,280
Nick. [sighs]

429
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:21,720
Hey, I'm going home. Is he okay?

430
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:24,240
-Yeah, he's all right, I think.
-Hey, I'm glad.

431
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:27,320
-[Nick] Another pint of lager, please.
-Sorry, mate, the bar's closed.

432
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:29,640
Shit.

433
00:25:33,120 --> 00:25:35,880
-I think everyone hates me.
-[sighs] Let's get you home.

434
00:25:37,760 --> 00:25:39,920
-Are you angry at me?
-No, I'm not. Come on.

435
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:42,400
-Sure?
-I'm not angry. I…

436
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:44,880
Let's just get an Uber or something.

437
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:47,480
What the fuck is wrong with him?

438
00:25:48,920 --> 00:25:50,280
I need to get him home.

439
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:53,560
Throw up in the car and I'll kill you.

440
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:55,360
[car keys jangling]

441
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:57,200
Come on.

442
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:00,800
[Nick breathes heavily, groans softly]

443
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:02,520
[door opens, closes]

444
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:04,400
Nick, open the door. [knocking]

445
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:06,800
[Nick retching]

446
00:26:07,320 --> 00:26:09,960
-[Nick retching]
-[David scoffs softly]

447
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:13,120
-[Nick groans] I'm fine.
-No, you're not. Let me in.

448
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:18,480
Charlie, it's not nice, okay?
You don't wanna be in here.

449
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:19,680
Yes, I do.

450
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:21,840
I don't care. Let me help you.

451
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:23,520
[yells] I don't need your help!

452
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:27,520
[breathes heavily]

453
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:29,840
Nick, let me in.

454
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:31,440
[Nick sighs]

455
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:36,600
[groans, grunts]

456
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:38,680
[toilet flushing]

457
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:40,480
[Nick] Sorry.

458
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:43,160
[Charlie] What happened?

459
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:45,320
[pensive music playing]

460
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:47,680
[sighs] I don't know. I just…

461
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:50,800
I got really drunk.

462
00:26:52,240 --> 00:26:55,320
[breathes shakily] The lads
kept giving me loads of shots,

463
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:59,920
and… and I saw that guy flirting with you,
and I just…

464
00:27:01,520 --> 00:27:03,320
I went crazy. [sighs]

465
00:27:04,560 --> 00:27:05,800
[Charlie] But why?

466
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:09,200
You know nothing would ever happen.

467
00:27:09,760 --> 00:27:12,840
[Nick inhales, exhales deeply]

468
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:14,720
[Charlie] Let's talk about it tomorrow.

469
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:18,880
[exhales slowly] I love knowing
that we have tomorrow.

470
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:25,120
[Charlie sighs]

471
00:27:39,560 --> 00:27:40,880
[music fades]

472
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,760
[sizzling in distance]

473
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,440
[cookware clattering]

474
00:27:58,720 --> 00:28:02,480
I thought you'd wanna sleep in.
You were so pissed last night.

